    • Method Detail

      • deserializeTranscriptDefinitionFile

        protected void deserializeTranscriptDefinitionFile()
                                            throws JannovarException,
                                                   HelpRequestedException
        Deserialize the transcript definition file, as configured in JannovarCommand.options. To run Jannovar, the user must pass a transcript definition file with the -D flag. This can be one of the files ucsc.ser, ensembl.ser, or refseq.ser (or a comparable file) containing a serialized version of the TranscriptModel objects created to contain info about the transcript definitions (exon positions etc.) extracted from UCSC, Ensembl, or Refseq and necessary for annotation.
        Throws:
        JannovarException - when there is a problem with the deserialization
        HelpRequestedException - when the user requested the help page
